  "text": "In a first phase [CITATION_1] , the identified 19 criteria were grouped into three subsets: effectiveness, efficiency, and satisfaction. Then, we reorganized them into a more accurate logical structure, obtaining 15 criteria grouped into four categories according to structure and arrangement, content appropriateness, multimodal output, and consistency issues. Many criteria visually affect the Web interface (e.g., colored areas or element magnifications), whereas others are exploited by the screen reader (e.g., hidden labels or names of frames). The criteria are reported next and labeled with the letter S if they refer specifically to screen reader navigation, with the letter M if they are linked only to magnifying features, and with the letter G if they refer both to screen readers and magnifiers (general use).",
